declarations.comments:
An `Attribute` describes some information about a node in the graph.
This type represents the structure for storing attributes, _not_
what attributes can be stored.
declarations.title: Attribute

declarations.comments: A node in the phylogeny graph.
declarations.title: Taxa

declarations.comments:
A Phylogeny graph with assocuated metadata.
Multiple trees may be stored by their roots.
declarations.title: Phylogeny

declarations.comments: Get the attribute map for a given `Taxa`.
declarations.title: attributes

declarations.comments:
Generate a GraphViz DOT representation of this phylogeny
For more information about DOT see this URL:
https://graphviz.org/doc/info/lang.html
declarations.title: dot

declarations.comments:
Get _all_ edges in a `Phylogeny`.
Note that this includes edges for disconnected trees.
declarations.title: edges

declarations.comments: Given a `Phylogeny` and a `ref` (identifier) get the `Taxa` for that `ref`.
declarations.title: lookupNode

declarations.comments: Get the root for each tree in a `Phylogeny`.
declarations.title: roots

declarations.comments:
Parse a phylogeny serialised with the Newick format.
Some variations of Newick are also supported.
declarations.title: parseNewick

declarations.comments: Parse a phylogeny serialised with the Nexus format
declarations.title: parseNexus

declarations.comments: Parse a phylogeny serialised with the PhyloXML format
declarations.title: parsePhyloXml

declarations.comments:
When a `ParseError` occurs, you can use this function to turn
it into a helpful error message. The second argument is the
input that failed parsing.

```purescript run
> lmap (parseNewick ")") (reportError ")")
Left ")\n^"
```
declarations.title: reportError

declarations.comments:
Get _all_ vertices (nodes) in a `Phylogeny`.
Note that this includes vertices from disconnected trees.
declarations.title: vertices

declarations.comments:
An `Attribute` describes some information about a node in the graph.
This type represents the structure for storing attributes, _not_
what attributes can be stored.
declarations.title: Attribute

declarations.comments:
Convert a `Text` attribute to a string, otherwise Nothing

```purescript run
> attributeToString (Text "hello")
Just "hello"

> attributeToString (Bool true)
Nothing
```
declarations.title: attributeToString

declarations.comments:
Convert a `Text` attribute to a string, otherwise Nothing

```purescript run
> attributeToBool (Text "hello")
Nothing

> attributeToBool (Bool true)
Just true
```
declarations.title: attributeToBool

declarations.comments: Convert an arbitrary string into an Attribute
declarations.title: parseAttribute

declarations.comments: Parse phylogenies serialised to the Newick format
declarations.title: parseNewick
